  "prompt": "What is a cake mix?",
  "response": "A cake mix is a pre-packaged combination of dry ingredients designed to simplify the process of baking a cake. Typically, a cake mix includes flour, sugar, baking powder, and flavorings. Some mixes may also contain dehydrated eggs, milk, or other ingredients. \n\nTo prepare a cake using a cake mix, you usually need to add a few wet ingredients such as water, oil, and eggs, although the specific requirements can vary depending on the brand and type of mix. After mixing the wet and dry ingredients together, the batter is poured into a baking pan and baked in the oven.\n\nCake mixes are popular because they save time and effort, making it easier for people to bake cakes at home without needing to measure out individual ingredients from scratch. They come in a variety of flavors, such as chocolate, vanilla, red velvet, and more, and can often be customized with additional ingredients like fruits, nuts, or frosting.",
